  <!-- ====== ABOUT / ORIGIN STORY (D7#3 / D9#6 — founder's own words) ====== -->
  <section class="lo-about lo-reveal" id="about">
    <div class="lo-about-inner">
      <div class="lo-section-eyebrow">Our story</div>
      <p class="lo-about-quote">“When I was born, there were <em>no digital cameras.</em>”</p>
      <div class="lo-about-body">
        <p>My mother built me and my siblings an actual, physical baby book. That book came out to embarrass me every birthday throughout my teenage years! It was embarrassing, but also fun, and I would secretly love hearing my parents talk about the things I did as a child.</p>
        <p>My daughter was born in the age of cell phones and digital cameras, and she didn't get a baby book. I noticed my wife, like almost all of the parents of this generation, would post pictures of my daughter daily on social media, displayed to everyone she knew.</p>
        <p>That's when the thought of Legacy Odyssey came into my head, and I started working on my daughter's own baby book website. Now I want to share these with all the parents out there. I hope you enjoy it.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lo-about-sign">Dan<small>Founder, Legacy Odyssey · Mesa, AZ</small></div>
    </div>
  </section>

