  <!-- ====== FAQ (D4#8 domain ownership transparency added) ====== -->
  <section class="lo-faq lo-reveal" id="help">
    <div class="lo-faq-inner">
      <div class="lo-faq-header">
        <div class="lo-section-eyebrow">Questions</div>
        <h2 class="lo-section-headline">Things parents <em>ask us</em></h2>
      </div>
      <details class="lo-faq-item"><summary>What exactly is a .com domain, and why does my child need one?</summary><p class="lo-faq-answer">A .com domain is a unique address on the internet — like "your-childs-name.com." Only one person can own each address. When you claim your child's name, nobody else can ever use that exact address. As they grow, it becomes their homepage and their identity online — and you'll have started it for them before they could walk.</p></details>
      <details class="lo-faq-item"><summary>Who actually owns the domain — and can my child have it later?</summary><p class="lo-faq-answer">Legacy Odyssey holds the registration and hosts the domain for you, registered in your child's name. You're never locked in — you can transfer it to another registrar at any time for a one-time $25 fee. When your child turns 18, you can move the domain to any registrar you choose, or keep it with us and we'll continue hosting it and help with anything they'd like to do with it.</p></details>
      <details class="lo-faq-item"><summary>Is the book private? Who can see it?</summary><p class="lo-faq-answer">Yes — the site is password-protected and hidden from search engines and image scrapers. Only people you share the password with can view it. You control who sees your child's book.</p></details>
      <details class="lo-faq-item"><summary>What if my child's exact name isn't available?</summary><p class="lo-faq-answer">You can get creative — add a middle name, a family name, or a nickname. Search variations right here on the site. Many parents use firstnamelastname.com or babyfirstname.com. There's almost always a great option available.</p></details>
      <details class="lo-faq-item"><summary>What happens if I cancel?</summary><p class="lo-faq-answer">After your introductory year at $29, the plan renews at $49.99/year (about $4.17/month). You can cancel anytime from your account and you'll keep full access to the site through the end of the period you've already paid for. After that, the site goes offline and the domain is released. We keep your photos and stories for up to a year so you can reactivate and pick up right where you left off — or, if you'd prefer, just ask us and we'll delete everything immediately. If you'd rather keep the domain, transfer it to another registrar before your term ends for a one-time $25 fee.</p></details>
      <details class="lo-faq-item"><summary>Can I give this as a gift?</summary><p class="lo-faq-answer">Absolutely — it's one of the most popular ways people use Legacy Odyssey. Buy a gift code for $29 and the recipient redeems it to pick their own domain and set up their book. It arrives as a digital gift code you can print or email.</p></details>
    </div>
  </section>

